day with his family\nLieutenant Carlton Buck and wife\narrived in the city this afternoon from\nHouston to visit relatives\nFashionable dressmaking childrens\nclothing a specialty Mrs F E\nBarnes No 2 Crawford street 18tf\nMlms Jackson who has recently fin\nished a business course at Dallas ar\nrived at his home here last night\nChas J Horn and wife of Houston\narrived in the city this afternoon to\nvisit Mrs Horns mother Mrs Allen\nMr and Mrs E Smith of Harvard\n111 and Mrs J F Going of Chicago\nare guests of Mrs Hancock In North\nPalestine\nLOST Friday night between the\nopera house and 509 Magnolia pair of\ngoldrimmed glasses Leave at latter\naddress and get reward 213t\nMiss Ila Morris has returned from\nWaco where she had been for some\nfew weeks in connection with the Sin\nger Sewing Machine company\nMrs Dan Gossett and family and\nMiss Mattie Love sister to Mrs Gos\nAINSLEE\nGUNTERS\nLIVING AGE\nEVERYBODYS\nTHE BOHEMIAN\nMETROPOLITAN\nALL SUNDAY PAPERS\nPOPULAR MECHANICS\nTECHNICAL WORLD MAGAZINE\nCOHENS PLACE\nWill Appreciate Your Patronage\nk\nJ\nn\nJ\nsett returned to Mart today after sev\neral days spent here with relatives\nAnton Hambusch of Granite City\n111 is here prospecting and may in\nvest in Anderson county property as\nhe is very favorably impressed with\nthis country\nRay Henninger and sister Mrs\nHess with her two children arrived\nthis morning from St Louis to visit\nMr C A Henninger Mr Ray Hen\nninger has been quite sick and hopes\nto be benefited by the change\nThe horses and carriage formerly\nowned by Mr G L Noble for sale If\nnot sold In next few days will be\nraffled Parties desiring this turnout\nwill apply to LC Ketcham 3t\nWANTED Energetic man to sell\nsewing machines Palestine and vicin\nity good pay references and bond\nrequired Address The Standard Sew\ning Machine Company No 1218 Olive\nstreet Saint Loius Mo 213t\nMessrs D R and W R Tucker are\nhome again from Kansas City where\nthey prepared themselves through the\nKansas City Veterinary College for\nwork in that profession They have\nopened office In this city with phone\nNo 71 residence phone 449 These\nyoung men announce that they are\nready for all work appertaining to\ntheir profession and that they offer\ntheir services to the people of Pales\ntine Anderson and the surrounding\ncounties 21lt\nSTATEMENT OF CONDITION OF THE\nPEOPLES BANK AND TRUST COMPANY\nOF PALESTINE TEXAS\nAT CLOSE OF BUSINESS FEBRUARY 14 1908\nLoans\nStocks and Bonds\nFurniture and Fixtures\nCash and Exchange\nResources\nChristian Church\nServices tomorrow at the\nhours\nSunday school 930 a m\nPreaching II a m and 745 p m\nJunior Endeavor 2 p m\nSenior Endeavor 630 p m\nBro Lockhart is with us His sub\nject in the morning will he The\nAbundant Power Mr Lintt will\nsing The Name of Jesus Is So Sweet\nThe subject of the evening sermon\nwill be Panics Tho solo will be\nThat Beautiful Land\nA Sunday school rally has been\nplanned for tomorrow and It is hoped\nthat at least five hundred will be\npresent at that service\nA cordial invitation is extended to\nall\nL D ANDERSON Pastor\nJunior Epworth League 3 p m\nSenior Epworth League 4 p m\nPrayer meeting Wednesday evening\n730 p m\nWomans Home Missionary Society\nevery Tuesday at 3 p m\nAll are Invited to attend and take\npart In these services\nTHOS R MOREHEAD Pastor\nBaptist Church\nThere will be preaching at the usual\nhours at the Avenue Baptist church\nand Mission by the pastor tomorrow\nDr Buckner of Buckners Orphan\nHome Dallas will preach at the\nmorning hour when an old folks ser\nvice will be hold in honor of Father\nG N McKay\nA D SPARKMAN Pastor\nCongregational Church\nSunday school at 945 a m R\nMarkle superintendent\nChristian Endeavor C30 p m\nMiss Maggie Miller president\nPreaching 11 a m and 730 p m\nPrayer meeting Thursday evening\nat 730\nKings Daughters meet on fourth\nTuesday in each month at 3 p m\nMrs Harriet Sivewright president\nC W MEYERS Pastor\nB\nPresbyterian Church\nServices at the usual hours Sunday\nChristian Science\nSunday services 3 p m\nWednesday services 8 p m\nCorner Oak and N Sycamore Sts\nBoard of Trade Rooms\nPublic cordially Invited\nMiss Kate Hunter will begin teach\ning music Thursday March 2Cth 2t\nfsma ms st smi\na body to the Avenue Baptist church\nto attend the old folks service in\nhonor of Father McKay All Union\nveterans are invited to join them\nMRS R J WALLACE DEAD\nGood Woman Died at Her Country\nHome Early This Afternoon\nNews reached the city early this\nafternoon of the death of Mrs R J\nWallace at the familys country home\nat about 130 oclock Mrs Wallace\nhad been sick for several months but\nher death was not expected The\nfamily lived in this city until a few\nmonths ago when Mr Wallace closed\nout his business and moved to his\nfarm They have hundreds of friends\nhere who will be grieved at Mrs Wal\nlaces death\nTho funeral will be held from C20\nChurch street tomorrow afternoon at\n3 oclock\nInterment in East Hill cemetery\nTEXAS NEWS NOTEST\nFive young men were arrested near\nHallville charged with having placed\nobstructions on the Texas Pacific\nti ack\nFrlck charged with the robbery of\nthe Graydon postoffico and arrested\nin Illinois has been landed in Hous\nton\nManager Pipkin of the Nona Mills\ncompany does not look for any decid\ned return of prosperity until after the\nelection\nFOR SALE Good horse and sur\nrey quick sale Address M at Her\nald office 213t\nGet the Habit Cook With Gas\nHouston Texas March 20 W X\nNorton J S Cleveland and G W Cal\nhoun three young men claiming to be\nfrom points in Illinois were arrested\nhere today charged with felony em\nbezzlement Chief of Police Ellis and\nthe city detectives think the arrests\nwill put an end to certain operations\nthat have been going on for about two\nweeks during which time six banks\nand fort v two large firms have con\ntributed on representations alleged to\nhave been made to a fund that was\nsupposed to be for charity Accord\ning to the police the only objects of\nsuch charity were those who are now\nbehind the bars\nComing from New Orleans and\nwith papers in their pockets that in\ndicate previous visits to Peoria III\nColumbus O and St Louis Mo two\nof the men appeared to be in distress\nwhen they faced the chief of police\nThe other Is said to have offered to\nsettle and return every cent collected\nin this city The amount Is believed\nto aggregate several hundred dollars\nIncidentally advices from New York\nindicate that the officers there would\nbe glad to hear from the men appre\nhended in this city\nBearing the credentials offered by\nSUNDAY AT CHURCHES\nr\nusual\nCentenary Methodist Church\nSunday school 930 a m\nPreaching at 11 a m and 730 p m\nJunior League 230 p m\nSenior League G30 p m\nThere will be given a cordial wel\ncome to all of these services Come\nand go with us and we will do you\ngood\nJ KILGORE Pastor\nGrace Methodist Church\nSchedule of services\nSunday school at 930 a m\nPreaching at 11 a m and 715 p m\nKeep a Written Ac\ncount of All Your\nExpenditures\nYou know from experience it\nis hard to save from your earn\nings but it can be done if you set\nyour heart and head in that di\nrection The only way to do it\nis to keep an account of what\nyou earn and what you spend\nThe simplest way to keep this\nrecord is to have a bank account\ndeposit your money with this\nbank and pay all bills by check\nYour bank book and returned\nchecks are the record you want\nthey will tell the story of your\nmoney both earned and spent\nNow would be the proper time\nto begin\nTo Attend Service\nThe Herald is requested to an\nnounce that members of John H\nReagan Camp No 44 U C V will\nmeet at their room tomororw at 1030\nfrom which place they will march in\nQuick Ne ws\nAt The GRAND LEADER\nBeginning Monday and as long as they last\nuntil Friday\n15cEmbroidered Handkerchiefs at 5c\n20c value in Bleached Turkish Towels 12ic\n35c value in Bleached Turkish Towels 19c\n160 White Embroidered Shirtwaists 79c\n25c Combination Skeleton WaistHttrpporters for\nchildren 15c\nGenuine Hydegrade Underskirts black 125\nSpecial Embroidery Counters Special\nLace Counters\nNew ReadytoWear Displays in Waists Skirts\nSuits Costumes\nThe Grand Leader\nPalestines Lea dingi Store\nOne Million\nSatisfied Shavers\nuse the Gillette Razor a sure sign of its superior\nitv A daily shave for less than 2 cents a week\nAlways Sharp Always Satisfying\nSet consists of Triple Silverplated Holders and 12\nDoubleedged Wafer Blades 24 shaving edges each\nblade good for an average of more than 20 satisfying\nshaves no matter how harsh the beard or tender your\nskin The only razor adjustable for a light or a close shave\nIf you use it 30 days and are not perfectly satisfied we\nwill return your money without question Every handle\nand blade fully guaranteed\nTriple Silverplated Holder and 12 Doubleedged Blades SS\nStandard Combination Set with Shaving Brush and Soap in Triple Silver\nplated Holders 7 SO\nExtra Blades 10 for 50c\nCOPELANDS JEWELRY STORE\nACHINERY\nShould you need Cotton Ginning Cane Grinding Saw Mill or other\nMachinery or repairs for same it matters not by whom made Dilleys\ncan save you time trouble or money perhaps all if you will consult\nthem You are desirious of building up Anderson County give proof of\nit by first giving home factories employing home labor an opportunity\nto serve you and thenKall things being equal give them the preference\nCall on or Address\nGeo M Dilley Son\nPalestine Tazag\nI TINGS BY APPOINTMENT\nWATKINS STUDIO\nRING 329\nMANY DOLLARS SECURED\nI\nIn the Name of Charity Three Men\nTaken In at Houston\nan organization of railroad employes\nthe trio are alleged to have visiteda\nmost every prominent man jn Hous\nton While the Railroad men believed\nthat they had engaged advertising\nagents to prepare a souvenir book on\na bisis of prorated profit It is said the\ncredentials were used to solicitsub\nscriptions for various amounts on the\nrepresentation that the fund was to\ngo to the relief of those former work\ners who by reason of stringent times\nwere out of employment\nThe complaint under which the ar\nrest was made sets forththe allega\ntion that 50 was secured from Presi\ndent Joe Rice of the Union Bank and\nTrust company It is said that the\nmoney was given as a donation and\non the representation described\nIn the possession of the men when\nsearched was found a list of fortyv\neight firms signed or stamped by rep\nresentatives After each the word\npaid appeared the amounts were\nomitted\nBought Noble Home\nIt was reported several days ago\nthat Air J D DuPuy of San Antonio\nhad bought the home of Mr G L\nNoble In Old Town This information\nIs confirmed by the recording of a\ndeed yesterday in which this beauti\nful home place Is conveyed to Mr Du\nPuy The consideration was G500\nWESELLtheBEST\nOF\nMen s\nShoes\nITS A HABIT\nOF OURS\nOur Shoes have character just as much as the man who\nwears them Choice Selected Leathers Skilled Shoe Build\ning Correct styles all the little points of detail to make\nthem Shoes with character Prices 3 50 to 6 Were\nready for the men who are ready for their Spring Shoes\nTake a Glance at Our Window\nDOYLE BROTHERS\nMENS OUTFITTERS\n404 Spring St\nS\n303 Main St\n1\nvm\na","height":"26948","width":"18064"}}
